  "prompt": "Why do you choose electrical engineering?",
  "response": "I chose electrical engineering because of my fascination with how electrical systems and electronics power and shape our modern world. From childhood, I was intrigued by gadgets and how they worked, which sparked my interest in understanding the principles behind electricity and electronics.\n\nElectrical engineering offers a broad and exciting field of study that ranges from power generation and transmission to telecommunications, control systems, and microelectronics. This diversity allows me to explore various areas and apply my skills in solving real-world problems, such as developing more efficient energy systems, improving communication technologies, or innovating in consumer electronics.\n\nMoreover, the field is constantly evolving with new technologies and challenges, providing endless opportunities for learning and growth. The potential to contribute to significant advancements in technology and to have a tangible impact on society was a compelling reason for me to pursue a career in electrical engineering.",
